==French==

===Etymology===
From {{inh|fr|fro|veoir}}, {{m|fro|veir}}, from earlier {{m|fro|vedeir}}, from {{inh|fr|la|vidēre}}, present active infinitive of {{m|la|videō}}, from {{inh|fr|itc-pro|*widēō}}, ultimately from {{der|fr|ine-pro|*weyd-}}. Unrelated to {{m|fr|voie}} and its derivatives and to {{m|fr|voirie}} or ''[[avoir]]''.

See cognates in regional languages in France : {{cog|nrf|veî}} or ''[[veir]]'', {{cog|roa-gal|vair}}, {{cog|pcd|vir}}, {{cog|roa-brg|voi}}, {{cog|frp|vêre}}, {{cog|oc|veire}} or ''[[véser]]'', {{cog|co|vedè}}.

